EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to education; authorizing one or more institutions
of higher education within the Nevada System of Higher
Education to establish a pilot program to assess the
competency of applicants for a license to teach through
the use of alternative assessment methods; requiring
certain regulations adopted by the Commission on
Professional Standards in Education to authorize an
applicant for a license to teach to be exempt from
requirements to pass a competency test in various subjects
if the applicant completes the pilot program; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Commission on Professional Standards in Education
2 and requires the Commission to adopt regulations prescribing the qualifications for
3 licensing teachers and other educational personnel. (NRS 391.011, 391.019)
4 Existing law additionally requires the Commission to adopt regulations governing
5 examinations for the initial licensing of teachers and other educational personnel.
6 (NRS 391.021) Existing regulations provide that an applicant is exempt from the
7 requirement to pass a competency test in the principles and methods of teaching if
8 the applicant submits to the Department of Education evidence that he or she: (1)
9 completed the “Principles of Learning and Teaching Test” prepared and
10 administered by the Educational Testing Service; or (2) is applying for a license
11 with an endorsement in an area for which training in the principles and methods of
12 teaching is not required. (NAC 391.036) Section 1 of this bill provides that the
