30 and is aligned with the criteria for designating a teacher as effective
31 or highly effective under the statewide performance evaluation
32 system established by the State Board of Education pursuant to
33 NRS 391.465;
34 (d) Require, for the duration of the pilot program, a teacher
35 selected to serve as a mentor pursuant to paragraph (b) to conduct a
36 monthly meeting with each participant who is assigned as his or her
37 mentee;
38 (e) For a participant to receive credit for satisfactorily
39 completing the pilot program, require the participant to, while he or
40 she is participating in the pilot program, receive at least two
41 consecutive evaluations, conducted pursuant to NRS 391.685, in
42 which the overall performance of the teacher was designated as
43 effective or highly effective;
